<body>

  <p class=3D"mediumtext">
    <span class=3D"maintitle">flat assembler</span><br>Open source assembly=
 language compiler.
  </p>

  <div class=3D"container">
    <p class=3D"largetext">
The flat assembler (abbreviated to fasm, intentionally stylized with lowerc=
ase letters) is a fast assembler running in a variety of operating systems,=
 in continued development since 1999.
It was designed primarily for the assembly of x86 instructions and it suppo=
rts x86 and x86-64 instructions sets with extensions like MMX, 3DNow!, SSE =
up to SSE4, AVX, AVX2, XOP, and AVX-512. It can produce output in plain bin=
ary, MZ, PE, COFF or ELF format.
It includes a powerful but simple macroinstruction system and does <a href=
=3D"https://board.flatassembler.net/topic.php?t=3D20249">multiple passes</a=
> to optimize the size of instruction codes.
The flat assembler is self-hosting and complete source code is included.
</p>

<p class=3D"largetext">
The only difference between flat assembler versions included in the followi=
ng packages is the operating system on which they can be run.
For any given source text each version is going to generate exactly the sam=
e output file, therefore every one of the following releases can be used to=
 compile programs for any operating system.
</p>

<div class=3D"links">
<table style=3D"width: 90%;">

  <colgroup>
    <col style=3D"width: 40%; max-width: 275px;">
    <col>
  </colgroup>

  <tbody><tr>
    <td>
<form action=3D"https://www.paypal.com/donate" method=3D"post" target=3D"_t=
op">

<input type=3D"image" src=3D"https://www.paypal.com/en_US/i/btn/btn_donate_=
LG.gif" border=3D"0" name=3D"submit" title=3D"PayPal - The safer, easier wa=
y to pay online!" alt=3D"Donate with PayPal button" style=3D"">
<img alt=3D"" border=3D"0" src=3D"https://www.paypal.com/en_US/i/scr/pixel.=
gif" width=3D"1" height=3D"1">
</form>
    </td>
    <td>
The flat assembler is made by a single person - Tomasz Grysztar - as a hobb=
y project. Although it is an open-source freeware, donations are appreciate=
d to help cover cost and time-loss.
It is a great help in maintaining this project.
If you would like to make a donation to the author, please click the button=
 beside.
    </td>
  </tr>

  <tr>
    <td>
      <a class=3D"boldlink" href=3D"https://flatassembler.net/fasmw17335.zi=
p">flat assembler 1.73.35 for Windows</a><br>
      <span class=3D"smalltext">size: 1038 kilobytes</span><br>
      <span class=3D"smalltext">last update: 24 Feb 2026 12:13:17 UTC</span=
>
    </td>
    <td>Apart from the command line version for Windows console this packag=
e contains the one with integrated syntax-highlighting editor,
so you can edit, compile and execute your programs from one place. It also =
contains the set of includes
with equates and macroinstructions for Windows programming and some example=
s of Windows programs created with
help of them. The provided documentation is in PDF format.</td>
  </tr>

  <tr>
    <td>
      <a class=3D"boldlink" href=3D"https://flatassembler.net/fasm-1.73.35.=
tgz">flat assembler 1.73.35 for Linux</a><br>
      <span class=3D"smalltext">size: 345 kilobytes</span><br>
      <span class=3D"smalltext">last update: 24 Feb 2026 12:13:26 UTC</span=
>
    </td>
    <td>This is a version for the Linux systems running on x86 or x64 compa=
tible processors.
Includes the documentation in pure ASCII format and some examples of Linux =
programs.</td>
  </tr>

  <tr>
    <td>
      <a class=3D"boldlink" href=3D"https://flatassembler.net/fasm17335.zip=
">flat assembler 1.73.35 for DOS</a><br>
      <span class=3D"smalltext">size: 450 kilobytes</span><br>
      <span class=3D"smalltext">last update: 24 Feb 2026 12:13:17 UTC</span=
>
    </td>
    <td>This version can be executed from command line of any operating sys=
tem compatible with DOS and contains
few tiny examples of DOS programs. It also contains the documentation in te=
xt format using DOS character set.
If you want to use flat assembler from the command line of Windows system, =
you should use the Windows console version instead of this one.</td>
  </tr>

  <tr>
    <td>
      <a class=3D"boldlink" href=3D"https://flatassembler.net/fasm-1.73.35.=
tar.gz">flat assembler 1.73.35 for Unix/libc</a><br>
      <span class=3D"smalltext">size: 277 kilobytes</span><br>
      <span class=3D"smalltext">last update: 24 Feb 2026 12:13:27 UTC</span=
>
    </td>
    <td>This is version for all platforms that have support for the ELF obj=
ect format and the C library, like OpenBSD or Zeta.
The object file provided in this package can be linked with the 32-bit C li=
brary to create the final executable
for any such system. The documentation in pure ASCII format is included.</t=
d>
  </tr>

</tbody></table>
</div>

<p class=3D"largetext">
flat assembler 2 is now available as a set of scripts and headers based on =
flat assembler g. Except for the macroinstruction syntax, it is largely com=
patible with flat assembler 1, while adding several new features.
See the <a href=3D"https://board.flatassembler.net/topic.php?t=3D22855">ded=
icated thread</a> for more information.
</p>


<div class=3D"links">
<table style=3D"width: 90%;">

  <colgroup>
    <col style=3D"width: 40%; max-width: 275px;">
    <col>
  </colgroup>

  <tbody><tr>
    <td>
      <a class=3D"boldlink" href=3D"https://flatassembler.net/fasm2.zip">fl=
at assembler 2 </a><br>
      <span class=3D"smalltext">size: 568 kilobytes</span><br>
      <span class=3D"smalltext">last update: 22 Apr 2026 18:21:00 UTC</span=
>
    </td>
    <td>This package (in continuous development) contains fasmg executables=
 for Windows and 64-bit Linux, with fasm2 shell scripts for both systems. I=
t also includes a version with integrated editor for Windows, automatically=
 configured to use fasm2 headers.</td>
  </tr>

</tbody></table>
</div>

<p class=3D"largetext">
flat assembler g (abbreviated to fasmg) is a new assembly engine designed a=
s a successor of the one used by flat assembler 1.
Instead of having a built-in support for x86 instructions, it implements th=
em through additional packages and in the same way it can be adapted to ass=
emble for <a href=3D"https://board.flatassembler.net/topic.php?t=3D19389">d=
ifferent architectures and purposes</a>.
With the included example packages it is capable of generating all the outp=
ut formats that flat assembler 1 could and additional ones, like Mach-O or =
Intel HEX.
</p>

<div class=3D"links">
<table style=3D"width: 90%;">

  <colgroup>
    <col style=3D"width: 40%; max-width: 275px;">
    <col>
  </colgroup>

  <tbody><tr>
    <td>
      <a class=3D"boldlink" href=3D"https://flatassembler.net/fasmg.l5p0.zi=
p">flat assembler g l5p0</a><br>
      <span class=3D"smalltext">size: 538 kilobytes</span><br>
      <span class=3D"smalltext">last update: 22 Apr 2026 18:12:26 UTC</span=
>
    </td>
    <td>This release contains executables for Linux, Windows and MacOS. It =
is packaged with examples of macroinstructions that allow assembly of simpl=
e programs for the architectures like x86, x64, 8052, AVR, or Java Virtual =
Machine. More examples and instructions set definitions for other architect=
ures can be found in the further sections of this website.</td>
  </tr>

</tbody></table>
</div>

<p class=3D"largetext">
The following are third-party products based on flat assembler, available t=
o download from their respective websites.
</p>

<div class=3D"links">
<table style=3D"width: 90%;">

  <colgroup>
    <col style=3D"width: 40%; max-width: 275px;">
    <col>
  </colgroup>

  <tbody><tr>
    <td>
      <a class=3D"boldlink" href=3D"http://arm.flatassembler.net/" target=
=3D"_blank">FASMARM</a><br>
    </td>
    <td>A cross-assembler for ARM architectures based on flat assembler 1, =
available in versions for Windows and Linux.</td>
  </tr>

</tbody></table>
</div>
